Reading from the equation:

- Center: $(h, k) = (2, -3)$ (note the sign change for $k$)

- Radius: $r^2 = 16$, so $r = 4$

To graph:

1. Plot the center at $(2, -3)$

2. From the center, count $4$ units in each direction (up, down, left, right)

3. Connect these four points with a smooth curve

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.6]
 % Grid
 (-4,-8) grid (8,2);
 % Axes
 (-4.5,0) – (8.5,0) node[right] {$x$};
 (0,-8.5) – (0,2.5) node[above] {$y$};
 % Circle
 (2,-3) circle (4);
 % Center
 ll[AtlasWarm] (2,-3) circle (4pt);
 at (2.2,-3) {$(2, -3)$};
 % Cardinal points
 ll[AtlasSage] (2,1) circle (3pt);
 ll[AtlasSage] (2,-7) circle (3pt);
 ll[AtlasSage] (-2,-3) circle (3pt);
 ll[AtlasSage] (6,-3) circle (3pt);
 % Tick marks
 in {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8} {
 (,0.1) – (,-0.1);
 }
 in {-8,-7,-6,-5,-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2} {
 (0.1,) – (-0.1,);
 }
